main event: On February 19, 1965, a large, fast-moving, flashing white light was observed for 11 minutes 55 miles west of Winnipeg, Canada.
interesting points: The sighting was reported by a Civil Airlines source., The object was described as very fast and large, with a brilliant white light., The observer was looking for a satellite when they noticed the fast-moving light., The object cut across an aircraft's flight path from 3 o'clock to 11 o'clock., The conclusion pointed towards the object being an aircraft.
sighted object: very fast large unsteady flashing white light
witness description: a member of the Royal Astronomical Society
